{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-post-jsx","path":"/videos/recipes/chinese-ginger-scallion-sauce","result":{"data":{"markdownRemark":{"html":"<p>Ginger scallion sauce is one of those go-to sauces you see at every Chinese restaurant.  It's especially popular in the Chinese barbecue shops that serve char siu, roasted duck and chicken -- you know, the ones that hang their meat right at the window for everyone to see.  You can always ask for a side of ginger scallion sauce to take home with your bbq-ed meats.</p>\n<p>I did a video (coming up) accompanying this recipe as well and in there, I used a rotisserie chicken I bought from the supermarket.  It is much easier and saves a lot of time, but the sauce does work best with a poached chicken that has less seasoning sicne the sauce is already salty.  This sauce is also a good way to use up chicken you used to make homemade chicken stock, if you do that kind of stuff.  I always thought it was such a waste that people threw whole chickens out.  Well, this sauce is the perfect condiment to that chicken...and really any bland meat you're looking to pick up.</p>\n<p><strong>Tips</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li>There's nothing too hard about the recipe.  Grating the ginger does take a while, but you can try smashing the ginger pieces and then chopping it up to save time.  </li>\n<li>Warming the oil just a bit before pouring it into the ginger and scallions will help all the flavors release, creating a better sauce.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>Directions</strong></p>\n<p><strong>1. Peel and grate ginger into a small bowl.</strong></p>\n<figure> <span class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\" style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;  max-width: 674px;\">\n      <a class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\" href=\"/static/121a23d213a7c40ed738856ebb1543c0/f9294/155-2.jpg\" style=\"display: block\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">\n    <span class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\" style=\"padding-bottom: 66.61721068249258%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url(&apos;data:image/jpeg;base64,&apos;); background-size: cover; display: block;\"></span>\n  <img class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\" alt=\"155 2\" title=\"155 2\" src=\"/static/121a23d213a7c40ed738856ebb1543c0/f9294/155-2.jpg\" srcset=\"/static/121a23d213a7c40ed738856ebb1543c0/90185/155-2.jpg 450w,\n/static/121a23d213a7c40ed738856ebb1543c0/f9294/155-2.jpg 674w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 674px) 100vw, 674px\" loading=\"lazy\">\n  </a>\n    </span> </figure>\n<p><strong>2. Cut scallions into small pieces omitting the very green tops.  Put into bowl with ginger.</strong></p>\n<figure> <span class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\" style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;  max-width: 726px;\">\n      <a class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\" href=\"/static/482d0958e91c7f4b75f593ef454e8750/4e1b0/155-3.jpg\" style=\"display: block\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">\n    <span class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\" style=\"padding-bottom: 66.66666666666666%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url(&apos;data:image/jpeg;base64,&apos;); background-size: cover; display: block;\"></span>\n  <img class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\" alt=\"155 3\" title=\"155 3\" src=\"/static/482d0958e91c7f4b75f593ef454e8750/4e1b0/155-3.jpg\" srcset=\"/static/482d0958e91c7f4b75f593ef454e8750/90185/155-3.jpg 450w,\n/static/482d0958e91c7f4b75f593ef454e8750/4e1b0/155-3.jpg 726w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 726px) 100vw, 726px\" loading=\"lazy\">\n  </a>\n    </span> </figure>\n<p><strong>3. Add in lemon juice, salt, sugar and soy sauce.</strong></p>\n<figure> <span class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\" style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;  max-width: 674px;\">\n      <a class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\" href=\"/static/61965ae20d0dfdd78a51da04bd3f31dc/f9294/155-4.jpg\" style=\"display: block\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">\n    <span class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\" style=\"padding-bottom: 66.61721068249258%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url(&apos;data:image/jpeg;base64,&apos;); background-size: cover; display: block;\"></span>\n  <img class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\" alt=\"155 4\" title=\"155 4\" src=\"/static/61965ae20d0dfdd78a51da04bd3f31dc/f9294/155-4.jpg\" srcset=\"/static/61965ae20d0dfdd78a51da04bd3f31dc/90185/155-4.jpg 450w,\n/static/61965ae20d0dfdd78a51da04bd3f31dc/f9294/155-4.jpg 674w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 674px) 100vw, 674px\" loading=\"lazy\">\n  </a>\n    </span> </figure>\n<p><strong>4. Heat oil in a small saucepan over medium to medium-high heat until just warmed.  Once heated, carefully pour oil into your ginger scallion mixture.</strong></p>\n<figure> <span class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\" style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;  max-width: 726px;\">\n      <a class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\" href=\"/static/31efd7d4d0ad0a2488e311ee6f70c8a7/4e1b0/155-5.jpg\" style=\"display: block\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">\n    <span class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\" style=\"padding-bottom: 66.66666666666666%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url(&apos;data:image/jpeg;base64,&apos;); background-size: cover; display: block;\"></span>\n  <img class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\" alt=\"155 5\" title=\"155 5\" src=\"/static/31efd7d4d0ad0a2488e311ee6f70c8a7/4e1b0/155-5.jpg\" srcset=\"/static/31efd7d4d0ad0a2488e311ee6f70c8a7/90185/155-5.jpg 450w,\n/static/31efd7d4d0ad0a2488e311ee6f70c8a7/4e1b0/155-5.jpg 726w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 726px) 100vw, 726px\" loading=\"lazy\">\n  </a>\n    </span> </figure>\n<p><strong>5. Serve over chicken.</strong></p>\n<figure> <span class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\" style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;  max-width: 726px;\">\n      <a class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\" href=\"/static/50294a776846ef37e2ca4957274b9cdf/4e1b0/155-6.jpg\" style=\"display: block\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">\n    <span class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\" style=\"padding-bottom: 66.66666666666666%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url(&apos;data:image/jpeg;base64,&apos;); background-size: cover; display: block;\"></span>\n  <img class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\" alt=\"155 6\" title=\"155 6\" src=\"/static/50294a776846ef37e2ca4957274b9cdf/4e1b0/155-6.jpg\" srcset=\"/static/50294a776846ef37e2ca4957274b9cdf/90185/155-6.jpg 450w,\n/static/50294a776846ef37e2ca4957274b9cdf/4e1b0/155-6.jpg 726w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 726px) 100vw, 726px\" loading=\"lazy\">\n  </a>\n    </span> </figure>\n<section class='recipe'>\n<p><strong>Ingredients</strong></p>\n<p>(makes 1/3 cup)</p>\n<ul><li>2 inches ginger</li><li>4 stalks of scallion</li><li>1 teaspoon lemon juice</li><li>2 teaspoons sugar</li><li>dash of salt</li><li>2 tablespoons soy sauce</li><li>1/4 cup oil</li></ul></section>","timeToRead":2,"excerpt":"Ginger scallion sauce is one of those go-to sauces you see at every Chinese restaurant.  It's especially popular in the Chinese barbecue…","frontmatter":{"title":"Chinese Ginger Scallion Sauce","image":{"feature":{"publicURL":"/static/155-1-560ec8b54ab247365c61167deb3ee648.jpg","childImageSharp":{"fluid":{"base64":"data:image/jpeg;base64,","aspectRatio":1.5,"src":"/static/560ec8b54ab247365c61167deb3ee648/b17c1/155-1.jpg","srcSet":"/static/560ec8b54ab247365c61167deb3ee648/00e5e/155-1.jpg 200w,\n/static/560ec8b54ab247365c61167deb3ee648/1a903/155-1.jpg 400w,\n/static/560ec8b54ab247365c61167deb3ee648/b17c1/155-1.jpg 800w,\n/static/560ec8b54ab247365c61167deb3ee648/7b761/155-1.jpg 933w","sizes":"(max-width: 800px) 100vw, 800px"}}}},"feature_video":null,"date":"2015-09-10","categories":["videos","recipes"],"tags":["recipes","sauces","ginger","scallion"]},"fields":{"slug":"/videos/recipes/chinese-ginger-scallion-sauce","date":"2015-09-09T23:00:00.000Z"}}},"pageContext":{"isCreatedByStatefulCreatePages":false,"slug":"/videos/recipes/chinese-ginger-scallion-sauce","nextslug":"/blog/5-course-back-to-school-meal","prevslug":"/videos/recipes/green-tea-tofu-mousse-cake"}}}